:: Limits, Risks, and Ethics {"position":"1850,875","size":"100,100"}
<h1 id="limits-risks-ethics">Limits, Risks, Ethics</h1>
<div class="scale-in-center">
<p>
Encryption is powerful, but it is not perfect. A system can still fail if people choose weak passwords, mishandle sensitive data, or fall for scams that reveal protected information. Encryption also raises ethical questions: it helps protect privacy and free expression, but it can also make criminal activity harder for governments to investigate. Because of that, encryption is often discussed not only as a technical tool, but also as a social and political issue.
</p>

</div>
<div class="slide-in-left">
<p>
