:: Why people encrypt information {"position":"425,325","size":"100,100"}
<h2 id="why-people-encrypt-information">Why people encrypt information</h2>
[[Main Lobby]] 

<p>Encryption can protect data at rest, in transit and while being processed, regardless of whether the data is in a computer system on-premises or in the cloud. For this reason, encryption has become critical to cloud security efforts and cybersecurity strategies more broadly.</p>
<p>According to the IBM® 2025 Cost of a Data Breach report, organizations that use encryption can reduce the financial impact of a data breach by over USD 200,000. </p>

<p>Deeper Dive: [[Plaintext vs ciphertext]]</p>

